Package neureka.calculus

Interface Function

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractBaseFunction, FunctionConstant, FunctionInput, FunctionNode, FunctionVariable
public interface Function
Besides the Tsr class, which is the core class of Neureka, this interface and its implementations represents the second most important feature of this library. Instances of Function implementations form an abstract syntax tree which is being built from a provided expression String containing function syntax. Just like functions in the mathematical sense, implementations of this interface receive inputs. Within the expression String needed for instantiation, these inputs are recognized by 'I[j]', 'Ij' or 'ij', where j is the input index. Functions accept arrays as their inputs, which is why variables must be targeted in such a way.
